  "texts": [
    "Mitra et al. (2019) employed CNNs to enhance microfossil classification for six species of Foraminifera, achieving over 80% accuracy.",
    "This study was notable because it utilized a large annotated dataset that trained the CNN to discern and classify subtle variations in fossil morphology and structure, often imperceptible with conventional methods.",
    "Similarly, Carvalho et al. (2020) leveraged DL for diatom microfossil classification, attaining high accuracy and revealing previously undetected morphological nuances.",
    "The model's adeptness at handling intricate, high-dimensional data facilitated a deeper comprehension of diatom species and their phylogenetic relationships.",
    "In another instance, Yasuhara et al. (2017) applied DL to analyze microfossil assemblages, yielding precise reconstructions of historical environmental and climatic conditions."
